ly%20in%20the%20%241%2C000%20per%20square%20foot%20range%20%E2%80%94%20but%20there%20are%20new%20buildings%20going%20up%20that%20are%20being%20listed%20at%20%242%2C000%20a%20square%20foot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20in%20a%20three-bedroom%2C%20two-bath%20apartment%20of%20maybe%201%2C900%20square%20feet%2C%20and%20we're%20paying%20%246%2C500%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Chicago%2C%20we%20had%20a%20three-bedroom%2C%20three-bathroom%2C%202%2C300%20square-foot%20condo%20on%20Michigan%20and%20Randolph.%20We%20looked%20out%20over%20the%20Lake%20Michigan%2C%2035th%20floor%2C%20and%20we%20were%20paying%20%245%2C000%20a%20month.%20So%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%20at%20the%20price%20for%20rentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChicago%20was%20a%20little%20bit%20bigger%20%E2%80%94%20and%20certainly%20a%20better%20location.%20We%20loved%20our%20location%20in%20Chicago%2C%20but%20we're%20also%20now%20three%20buildings%20from%20the%20beach.%20So%20we're%20going%20to%20pay%20a%20premium%20for%20that%20and%20the%20area%20that%20we're%20in.%20But%20it's%20certainly%20more%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I'm%20sitting%20around%20doing%20work%20at%20home%20and%20most%20people%20are%20going%20for%20a%20coffee%2C%20I%20just%20walk%20outside%20to%20the%20beach%20for%2010%20minutes%20and%20soak%20up%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225e4e1620-1422-41ec-a47c-c5711cc1ca05%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20unexpected%20quirks%20to%20living%20in%20Puerto%20Rico%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20that%20different%20here%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20it's%20between%2070%20and%2090%20degrees%20all%20year%20round.%20The%20coldest%20day%20on%20record%20in%20San%20Juan%20was%2064%20degrees%2C%20and%20the%20hottest%20day%20on%20record%20was%2096%20degrees.%20Compare%20that%20to%20Florida.%20I%20was%20in%20Florida%20when%20it%20was%20in%20the%2050s%20and%20it%20was%20freezing.%20And%20then%20Florida%20can%20hit%20110%20degrees.%20So%20can%20Texas%20and%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20it's%20similar%20to%20Hawaii%20in%20that%20it%20stays%20the%20same%20temperature%20year%20round.%20If%20I%20go%20on%20my%20weather%20app%20right%20now%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20say%2077%20to%2087%20degrees%20for%20the%20next%2010%20days.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20really%20nice.%20It%20doesn't%20get%20too%20hot%20and%20it%20never%20gets%20too%20cold.%20It's%20humid%2C%20but%20not%20like%20Florida-humid.%20So%2C%20the%20weather%20is%20fantastic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20wonderful%20restaurants%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20a%20great%20surprise%20coming%20from%20Chicago.%20Any%20ethnicity%20that%20you%20want%2C%20and%20then%20very%2C%20very%20high-quality%20fancy%20restaurants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChicago%20is%20a%20very%20clean%20city%2C%20and%20San%20Juan%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I'm%20talking%20specifically%20the%20San%20Juan%20area%20%E2%80%94%20is%20not%20the%20cleanest.%20There's%20graffiti%2C%20but%20that's%20typical%20of%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20just%20came%20back%20from%20Portugal%2C%20and%20they%20get%20graffiti%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20infrastructure%20on%20the%20island%20has%20certainly%20been%20neglected%20%E2%80%94%20you've%20probably%20heard%20about%20their%20power%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Condos%20on%20the%20water%20in%20Puerto%20Rico.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68769522f748d8c055f5a711%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Michael%20McCready%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20there%20on%20New%20Year's%20Eve%20and%20the%20power%20went%20out.%20I%20was%20there%20at%20Easter%20and%20the%20power%20went%20out.%20And%20it%20was%20out%20for%20two%20or%20three%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20power%20went%20out%20almost%20across%20the%20island.%20My%20son%20and%20I%20were%20driving%20to%20the%20eastern%20part%20of%20the%20island%20on%20New%20Year's%20and%20none%20of%20the%20traffic%20lights%20were%20working%20and%20all%20the%20restaurants%20were%20closed.%20Nobody%20had%20any%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20I%20live%2C%20we%20all%20have%20full%20building%20generators.%20So%20when%20the%20power%20goes%20out%2C%20it%20literally%20goes%20and%20comes%20right%20back%20on.%20So%20there%20was%20absolutely%20no%20disruption%20for%20us.%20But%20there%20was%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20on%20the%20island.%20If%20you've%20got%20no%20air%20conditioning%20and%20you've%20got%20no%20electricity%20for%20three%20days%2C%20your%20refrigerator%2C%20your%20food%20is%20gone%2C%20you're%20sweltering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20of%20parasailing%20in%20Puerto%20Rico.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68769522f748d8c055f5a710%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20view%20of%20the%20ocean%20in%20Puerto%20Rico.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Michael%20McCready%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGroceries%20tend%20to%20be%20a%20little%20bit%20higher%20priced.%20Apparently%2C%20there's%20some%20law%20that%20says%20food%20has%20to%20go%20to%20the%20US%20mainland%20first%20before%20it%20comes%20to%20Puerto%20Rico.%20Even%20if%20they%20could%20get%20something%20from%20the%20Dominican%20Republic%2C%20it%20has%20to%20go%20through%20the%20mainland%20in%20order%20to%20get%20to%20Puerto%20Rico.%20And%20that%20transportation%20cost%20is%20going%20to%20be%20reflected%20in%20the%20cost%20of%20goods.%20But%20there's%20a%20Costco%20here%2C%20and%20Amazon%20delivers%20here.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20really%20not%20much%20difference%20than%20living%20on%20the%20mainland.%20We've%20been%20there%20for%20seven%20months%20now%2C%20and%20that%20experience%20has%20proven%20correct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20fantastic%20move%20for%20us%20and%20we%20couldn't%20be%20happier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3C