0stop%20offering%20new%20Office%20features%20to%20these%20Windows%20users%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752658705000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-122569690%2Cimgsize-43220.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fmicrosoft-will-stop-offering-new-office-features-to-these-windows-users-starting-august-2026%2Farticleshow%2F122569788.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Microsoft%20will%20cease%20delivering%20new%20features%20to%20Office%20apps%20on%20Windows%2010%20starting%20August%202026%2C%20pushing%20users%20towards%20Windows%2011.%20While%20security%20updates%20continue%20until%20October%202028%2C%20feature%20development%20freezes%2C%20impacting%20Microsoft%20365%20Personal%2C%20Family%2C%20and%20enterprise%20users%20differently.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fmicrosoft-will-stop-offering-new-office-features-to-these-windows-users-starting-august-2026%2Farticleshow%2F122569788.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20millennial%20couple%20has%20lived%20'for%20free'%20in%20their%20own%20home%20for%2010%20years%20by%20house%20hacking.%20The%20savings%20are%20allowing%20them%20to%20build%20their%20dream%20home.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22todd%20baldwin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F629932b6e319620018a84d4f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESeattle-based%20couple%20Todd%20and%20Angela%20Baldwin.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Todd%20Baldwin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETodd%20and%20Angela%20Baldwin%20haven't%20paid%20for%20housing%20since%202015%2C%20thanks%20to%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hacking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHouse%20hacking%20involves%20renting%20extra%20rooms%20or%20units%20to%20offset%20or%20eliminate%20your%20mortgage%20payment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESaving%20big%20on%20housing%20is%20allowing%20them%20to%20build%20their%20dream%20home%20on%20a%202.5-acre%20plot%20of%20land.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHousing%20is%20the%20largest%20expense%20for%20most%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fcesan.nr0.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20last%20consumer%20expenditures%3C%2Fa%3E%20survey%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%2C%20it%20accounted%20for%2032.9%25%20of%20total%20household%20budgets%20in%202023.%20For%20Todd%20and%20Angela%20Baldwin%2C%20it's%20been%200%25%20for%20the%20past%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20actually%20never%20owned%20a%20property%20where%20we%20have%20a%20mortgage%20that%20isn't%20paid%20for%20by%20our%20tenants%2C%26quot%3B%20Todd%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20He%20explained%20how%20they've%20managed%20to%20eliminate%20that%20major%20expense%20for%20years%2C%20and%20how%20it's%20changed%20their%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222cade5b3-3d41-4c78-a8a2-d4aa26d01d6b%5C%22%3ELiving%20for%20free%20in%20their%20own%20home%20by%20'house%20hacking'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Baldwins%20bought%20their%20first%20home%20%E2%80%94%20a%206-bed%2C%204-bath%20outside%20Seattle%20%E2%80%94%20in%20December%202015.%20They%20moved%20into%20the%20master%20bedroom%2C%20kept%20the%20smallest%20room%20as%20an%20office%2C%20and%20rented%20the%20remaining%20four%20rooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20strategy%20is%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hacking%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20you%20rent%20extra%20rooms%20(if%20you're%20living%20in%20a%20single-family%20home)%20or%20units%20(if%20you're%20living%20in%20a%20multi-family%20home)%20in%20order%20to%20offset%20or%20completely%20eliminate%20your%20housing%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20in%20the%20Baldwins'%20case%2C%20turn%20your%20primary%20residence%20into%20an%20income-producing%20asset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20house%20pays%20us%20%245%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20so%20%2460%2C000%20a%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Baldwin%2C%20noting%20that%20they've%20since%20sold%20their%20first%20home%20and%20bought%20a%20duplex%20to%20accommodate%20their%20growing%20family.%20Now%2C%20instead%20of%20sharing%20a%20kitchen%20and%20common%20space%2C%20they%20live%20in%20their%20own%20unit%20with%20their%20two%20kids%20and%20rent%20the%20other%20half%20of%20their%20duplex%20on%20Airbnb.%20They%20also%20converted%20their%20garage%20into%20a%20studio%20apartment%20that%20they%20list%20as%20a%20short-term%20rental.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20depreciation%2C%20that's%20all%20tax-free%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20rental%20property%20depreciation%20deduction.%20The%20way%20he%20sees%20it%2C%20the%20%2460%2C000%20in%20annual%20rental%20income%20is%20about%20what%20he%20would%20take%20home%20if%20he%20had%20a%20%24100%2C000%20salary%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20if%20we%20look%20at%20the%20net%20income%20we%20make%20from%20living%20in%20our%20house%2C%20it's%20like%20our%20house%20is%20a%20%24100%2C000%20salary.%20But%20it's%20more%20than%20that%20because%2C%20also%2C%20our%20mortgage%20is%20free.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c7a0e28d-9cdf-41bb-9e16-1489d1136899%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Bullish%20on%20Airbnb'%3A%20Listing%20short-term%20rentals%20vs.%20long-term%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20their%20two%20Airbnb%20listings%2C%20they%20bring%20in%20about%20%249%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20said%20Baldwin%3A%20%26quot%3BSome%20months%20it%20might%20be%20like%20%248%2C900%2C%20some%20months%20it%20might%20be%20like%20%249%2C400.%26quot%3B%20BI%20reviewed%20a%20copy%20of%20their%20June%20earnings%20report%20from%20Airbnb%2C%20showing%20%249%2C500%20in%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20their%20units%20were%20rented%20to%20long-term%20tenants%2C%20he%20estimates%20they'd%20bring%20in%20about%20half%20of%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20long-term%20rentals%2C%20which%20they%20reverted%20to%20during%20Covid%20when%20people%20stopped%20traveling%2C%20Airbnb%20is%20%26quot%3Bway%20more%20lucrative%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20It%20helps%20that%20their%20occupancy%20rate%20is%20high%2C%20which%20he%20credits%20to%20the%20property's%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20love%20to%20have%20my%20ego%20stroked%20and%20say%20we're%20awesome%20hosts%2C%20but%20I%20think%20we%20just%20lucked%20out%20with%20this%20building%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%2010%20minutes%20from%20the%20Seattle-Tacoma%20airport%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20directly%20in%20the%20flight%20path.%20We%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20coming%20to%20stay%20because%20it's%20so%20close%20to%20the%20airport%2C%20but%20then%20you%20can%20take%20an%20Uber%20and%20get%20downtown%20in%2020%20minutes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20another%20benefit%20of%20listing%20his%20units%20on%20Airbnb%20is%20that%20it%20protects%20him%20from%20dealing%20with%20potential%20squatters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAirbnb%20guests%20are%20just%20that%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20guests%2C%20not%20tenants.%20So%2C%20they%20don't%20have%20tenant%20rights%20and%20they%20don't%20have%20squatters'%20rights%2C%20for%20example%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Baldwin.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20if%20an%20Airbnb%20guest%20stays%20three%20nights%20and%20then%20refuses%20to%20leave%2C%20they%20cannot%20legally%20claim%20squatter's%20rights%20because%20there's%20no%20lease.%20For%20me%2C%20not%20only%20do%20I%20make%20double%20to%20triple%20the%20income%2C%20I'm%20also%20protected%20against%20people%20trying%20to%20squat%20and%20stay%20in%20my%20property%20and%20not%20pay.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20investors%20prefer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investing-increasing-cash-flow-mid-term-rentals-airbnb-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emid-%20or%20long-term%20rentals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20less%20hands-on%20and%20less%20risky%2C%20Baldwin%20says%20he's%20%26quot%3Bvery%20bullish%20on%20Airbnb.%26quot%3B%20It%20still%20takes%20time%2C%20effort%2C%20and%20money%20to%20set%20one%20up%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bif%20the%20building%20is%20right%2C%20the%20property%20is%20right%2C%20and%20the%20location%20is%20good%2C%20anyone%20can%20make%20it%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22todd%20baldwin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63b5df2b7f62b200191a56a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBaldwin%20splits%20his%20time%20between%20raising%20his%20two%20kids%20and%20building%20his%20family's%20dream%20home.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Todd%20Baldwin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223ca094cc-22e2-4960-af50-e61a31e4a274%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuilding%20their%20dream%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20without%20having%20to%20worry%20about%20a%20mortgage%20has%20changed%20the%20Baldwins'%20financial%20situation%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20allowed%20Todd%20to%20take%20a%20step%20back%20from%20work%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-how-wholesaling-works-earn-money-investing-investor-property-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewholesaling%20real%20estate%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20his%20primary%20source%20of%20income%20%E2%80%94%20and%20divide%20his%20time%20between%20%26quot%3Bdad%20mode%20and%20building%20our%20dream%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20hire%20a%20general%20contractor%20for%20the%20dream%20house%2C%20which%20will%20include%20an%20infinity%20pool%20waterslide%2C%20barn%20with%20a%20bowling%20lane%2C%20movie%20theater%2C%20and%20a%20cottage%20off%20the%20main%20home%20for%20his%20mom%20to%20live%20in%2C%20he's%20doing%20all%20the%20work%20himself.%20When%20his%20family%20moves%20in%20in%20the%20next%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20he%20plans%20to%20keep%20the%20duplex%20and%20list%20the%20unit%20they're%20currently%20living%20in%20on%20Airbnb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20his%20wife%20bought%20the%20land%20%E2%80%94%202.5%20acres%20overlooking%20the%20Puget%20Sound%20%E2%80%94%20for%20%24735%2C000%20in%20cash.%20He%20said%20his%20wholesale%20deals%20helped%20with%20the%20purchase%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20no%20way%20that%20we%20would%20be%20able%20to%20pay%20cash%20had%20we%20not%20lived%20for%20free%20for%20so%20long%20and%20been%20really%20smart%20with%20our%20investing%20strategy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaldwin%20encourages%20all%20aspirational%20investors%20to%20consider%20house-hacking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20I'm%20drinking%20the%20Kool-Aid%20a%20bit%2C%20but%20I%20think%20everybody%20should%20live%20for%20free%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20of%20it%20this%20way%3A%20You%20need%20some%20place%20to%20live.%20You're%20either%20going%20to%20pay%20off%20someone%20else's%20mortgage%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20called%20renting%20%E2%80%94%20you're%20going%20to%20pay%20off%20your%20own%20mortgage%2C%20which%20is%20living%20in%20your%20house%20but%20not%20monetizing%20it%2C%20or%20other%20people%20are%20going%20to%20pay%20off%20your%20mortgage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt'll%20mean%20sharing%20space%20with%20roommates%20%E2%80%94%20and%20potentially%20many%20different%20roommates%20if%20you%20use%20Airbnb%20and%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20tenant%20turnover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20mind%20Airbnb%20and%20having%20a%20stranger%20in%20the%20unit%20below%20you%20or%20across%20the%20hall%20from%20you%2C%20then%20financially%20speaking%2C%20it's%20a%20no-brainer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BHaving%20other%20people%20pay%20off%20your%20mortgage%20seems%20like%20this%20crazy%20loophole%2C%20and%20it%20honestly%20surprises%20me%20that%2