s%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flove-island-fans-love-amaya-papaya-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esurveil%20your%20every%20move%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20hopes%20they'll%20pick%20you%20(yikes).%20Think%20of%20it%20more%20like%20building%20and%20leaning%20on%20relationships%20so%20that%20a%20hiring%20manager%20might%20give%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-search-tips-flexibility-career-advancement-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyour%20job%20application%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20approach%20is%20often%20more%20effective%20than%20expecting%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20to%20do%20the%20talking%20for%20you%2C%20career%20advisors%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20And%20this%20is%20especially%20the%20case%20if%20you're%20just%20starting%20out%20and%20don't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20hire%20people%2C%20they%20don't%20hire%20paper%2C%26quot%3B%20Andy%20Chan%2C%20who%20runs%20the%20Office%20of%20Personal%20and%20Career%20Development%20at%20Wake%20Forest%20University%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20job%20seekers%20too%20often%20think%20of%20recruiting%20and%20applying%20for%20jobs%20as%20transactional%20processes.%20While%20they%20are%2C%20to%20some%20degree%2C%20Chan%20said%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20try%20to%20ground%20your%20interactions%20with%20an%20employer%20in%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20No.%201%20way%20to%20get%20an%20interview%20is%20to%20know%20someone%20at%20an%20organization%20or%20have%20someone%20recommend%20that%20you%20talk%20to%20someone%20at%20a%20specific%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20conversation%2C%20Chan%20said%2C%20the%20person%20you%20spoke%20with%20might%20then%20talk%20to%20the%20hiring%20manager%20or%20someone%20in%20human%20resources%20and%20let%20them%20know%20you're%20applying%2C%20Chan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20bit%20of%20endorsement%20is%20frequently%20the%20key%20to%20getting%20an%20interview%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223cf13a66-2548-4b02-86e8-b9d1d00e7d20%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpend%2060%25-70%25%20of%20your%20time%20networking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChan%20said%20it's%20important%20that%20most%20job%20seekers%2C%20including%20those%20seeking%20their%20first%20professional%20role%2C%20spend%20about%2060%25%20to%2070%25%20of%20their%20time%20talking%20with%20people%20and%20only%2030%25%20to%2040%25%20applying%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20students%20will%20say%2C%20'Whoa%2C%20I%20spent%20like%20100%25%20of%20my%20time%20online%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20some%20will%20then%20say%20that%20their%20approach%20hasn't%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20have%20many%20contacts%20in%20your%20field%2C%20college%20career%20offices%20can%20often%20help%20connect%20you%20with%20relevant%20alumni%20and%20corporate%20recruiters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20try%20to%20make%20connections%20by%20asking%20someone%20you%20admire%20to%20chat%20for%20a%20few%20minutes%20about%20their%20career%20trajectory.%20It's%20what's%20sometimes%20called%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsummer-associate-recruiting-white-and-case-hiring-interview-questions-virtual-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einformational%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20make%20sure%20you%20do%20your%20homework%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetworking-dos-and-donts-tips-advice-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eresearching%20the%20employer%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20person%20you're%20speaking%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20going%20to%20ask%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetworking-dos-and-donts-tips-advice-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E15%20minutes%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20their%20time%2C%20be%20sure%20to%20show%20that%20you%20spent%2015%20minutes%20of%20yours%2C%26quot%3B%20Madeline%20Mann%2C%20a%20career%20coach%20and%20CEO%20of%20Self%20Made%20Millennial%2C%20previously%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22411078e4-a60e-439f-a3c3-db2182aaa9f5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EApply%2C%20then%20start%20your%20hustle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJane%20Curran%2C%20global%20head%20of%20HR%20operations%20at%20the%20real-estate%20company%20JLL%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20job%20seekers%20still%20need%20to%20apply%20for%20jobs%20that%20make%20sense%20for%20them.%20After%20all%2C%20you%20need%20to%20be%20on%20an%20employer's%20radar%20to%20be%20in%20contention.%20Yet%2C%20she%20said%2C%20there's%20more%20work%20to%20do%20after%20submitting%20an%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThen%20you%20have%20to%20turn%20that%20into%20a%20hustle%2C%26quot%3B%20Curran%20said.%20That%20could%20mean%20going%20to%20LinkedIn%20to%20see%20who%20might%20have%20a%20connection%20at%20that%20company%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20go%20figure%20out%20who%20knows%20who%2C%20and%20how%20am%20I%20going%20to%20stand%20out%3F%20How%20am%20I%20going%20to%20get%20a%20job%20interview%3F%26quot%3B%20Curran%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatherine%20Fisher%2C%20a%20career%20expert%20with%20LinkedIn%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20networking%20doesn't%20have%20to%20mean%20taking%20someone%20out%20to%20dinner%20three%20nights%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20or%20keeping%20a%20connection%20with%20someone%20can%20involve%20small%20gestures%20like%20offering%20a%20substantive%20comment%20on%20someone's%20post%20or%20shooting%20them%20a%20text%2C%20Fisher%20said.%20Other%20times%2C%20like%20if%20you're%20asking%20someone%20for%20a%20bigger%20favor%2C%20it%20might%20be%20time%20to%20buy%20them%20a%20coffee%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNetworking%20is%20a%20muscle%20that%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20flex%20throughout%20your%20entire%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20Fisher%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20job%20searching%2C%