0seemed%20very%20important%20in%20the%201990s%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20when%20the%20internet%20was%20brand-new%20%E2%80%94%20but%20doesn't%20seem%20top%20of%20mind%20right%20now%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20won't%20tell%20me.%20A%20rep%20there%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20existence%20of%20the%20company's%20browser%20project%2C%20or%20anything%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20people%20who%20spend%20their%20time%20working%20on%20browsers%20think%20OpenAI's%20plan%20is%20straightforward%3A%20Like%20other%20AI%20companies%2C%20OpenAI%20says%20it%20will%20make%20virtual%20assistants%20that%20can%20learn%20about%20you%2C%20figure%20out%20what%20you%20need%2C%20and%20provide%20it%20whenever%20you%20need%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-agentic-ai-agents-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eagentic%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20future%20AI%20people%20keep%20talking%20about.%20And%20in%20order%20to%20do%20that%2C%20it%20will%20need%20to%20peer%20into%20your%20life%2C%20and%20it%20will%20need%20to%20access%20all%20sorts%20of%20data%20and%20sites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20app%20can't%20do%20that.%20But%20a%20browser%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20can%20%E2%80%94especially%20for%20people%20who%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20using%20their%20computers%20for%20work%2C%20shopping%2C%20and%20other%20high-value%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20on%20a%20browser%20right%20now%2C%20think%20of%20how%20many%20other%20tabs%20you%20have%20open%2C%20and%20how%20much%20data%20each%20one%20of%20them%20contains%20about%20you%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20the%20sites%20you%20visit%2C%20but%20the%20spreadsheets%20and%20docs%20you're%20working%20on%2C%20and%2For%20how%20you%20manage%20your%20finances%20and%20everything%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20believe%20that%20AI%20agents%20are%20going%20to%20be%20the%20future%20of%20our%20industry%2C%20those%20agents%20will%20need%20two%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Josh%20Miller%2C%20CEO%20of%20The%20Browser%20Company.%20%26quot%3BThey%20will%20need%20access%20to%20the%20tools%20you%20use%20every%20day%2C%20and%20they%20need%20to%20be%20with%20you%20as%20you're%20doing%20your%20work%2C%20so%20they%20have%20context.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20for%20those%20same%20reasons%2C%20some%20tech%20folks%20argue%2C%20OpenAI%20owning%20a%20browser%20isn't%20just%20nice%20to%20have%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20crucial%20part%20of%20the%20company's%20plans.%20It's%20also%20a%20way%20to%20protect%20itself%20if%20competitors%20like%20Apple%20or%20Google%20%E2%80%94%20who%20have%20their%20own%20AI%20agendas%20%E2%80%94%20limit%20OpenAI's%20access%20to%20their%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20announcing%20you%20have%20a%20browser%20is%20different%20from%20getting%20people%20to%20switch%20browsers%2C%20which%20isn't%20something%20most%20people%20do%20willingly%20or%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20normal%20person%2C%20you%20likely%20haven't%20thought%20about%20which%20browser%20you%20use%20in%20some%20time%20%E2%80%94%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgs.statcounter.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprobably%3C%2Fa%3E%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fanalytics.wikimedia.org%2Fdashboards%2Fbrowsers%2F%23all-sites-by-browser%2Fbrowser-family-and-major-hierarchical-view%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChrome%2C%20Google's%20browser%2C%20or%20Safari%2C%20the%20Apple%20browser%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20comes%20as%20the%20default%20option%20on%20iPhones%20and%20MacBooks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20that%2C%20you%20may%20have%20used%20Netscape%20Navigator%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20browser%20many%20people%20used%20to%20get%20on%20the%20web%20%E2%80%94%20or%20Internet%20Explorer%20%E2%80%94%20Microsoft's%20answer%20to%20Netscape%2C%20which%20it%20promoted%20aggressively%20(and%2C%20the%20US%20government%20argued%20in%20court%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FUnited_States_v._Microsoft_Corp.%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520U.S.%2520government%2520accused%2520Microsoft%2Csuch%2520as%2520Netscape%2520and%2520Java.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eillegally%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20periodically%2C%20people%20keep%20trying%20to%20introduce%20new%20browsers.%20Brave%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20launched%20in%202016%20by%20promoting%20itself%20as%20an%20ad-blocker%2C%20but%20has%20since%20emphasized%20connections%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrave.com%2Fwallet%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrypto%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Browser%20Company%20launched%20its%20Arc%20Browser%20widely%20in%202023%2C%20pitching%20it%20as%20a%20browser%20for%20people%20who%20were%20frustrated%20with%20Chrome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBrowser%20markets%20are%20immortal%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Brave%20CEO%20Brendan%20Eich%2C%20arguing%20that%20opportunities%20for%20new%20entrants%20pop%20up%20every%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrave%20says%20they%20now%20have%20more%20than%2090%20million%20active%20users%20%E2%80%94%20not%20huge%2C%20but%20enough%20to%20crack%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftaptwicedigital.com%2Fblog%2Fbrave-usage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elists%20of%20browsers%20ranked%20by%20market%20share%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20The%20Browser%20Company%20has%20announced%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrowsercompany.substack.com%2Fp%2Fletter-to-arc-members-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20is%20moving%20on%20from%20Arc%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20focus%20on%20Dia%2C%20a%20new%2C%20AI-first%20browser.%20Miller%20says%20Arc%20topped%20out%20at%20a%20%26quot%3Bfew%20million.%26quot%3B%20He%20says%20the%20company%20immediately%20found%20a%20group%20of%20fans%20willing%20to%20spend%20time%20learning%20how%20to%20use%20its%20complicated%20set%20of%20features%2C%20and%20loved%20it%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20it%20struggled%20to%20find%20more%20users%20after%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20Eich%20nor%20Miller%20has%20a%20silver%20bull