ustainable-mud-house%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epermaculture%2C%20an%20agricultural%20design%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20on%20natural%20ecosystems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CPermaculture%20is%20about%20working%20with%20nature%2C%20not%20fighting%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20Neil%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20focus%20on%20creating%20a%20self-sustaining%20system%20that%20nurtures%20the%20soil%2C%20supports%20biodiversity%2C%20and%20produces%20food%20and%20resources%20without%20harm.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20five%20years%2C%20they%20changed%20three%20acres%20of%20degraded%20land%20into%20a%20lush%20farm.%20Through%20composting%2C%20cover%20cropping%2C%20mulching%2C%20and%20planting%20a%20diversity%20of%20crops%20and%20trees%2C%20they%20added%20over%2030%20tonnes%20of%20organic%20matter%20to%20the%20soil.%20This%20increased%20the%20soil%E2%80%99s%20organic%20carbon%20content%2C%20an%20essential%20factor%20for%20long-term%20carbon%20sequestration%20and%20soil%20health%2C%20by%20approximately%20half%20to%20one%20percent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWatching%20the%20soil%20come%20back%20to%20life%20has%20been%20the%20most%20rewarding%20part%2C%E2%80%9D%20Momo%20says.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20earth%20is%20resilient%20when%20you%20treat%20it%20with%20respect.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20farm%20grows%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20vegetables%2C%20fruits%2C%20and%20native%20plants.%20Leafy%20greens%20like%20spinach%2C%20kale%2C%20fenugreek%2C%20and%20mustard%20grow%20alongside%20cruciferous%20vegetables%20such%20as%20cabbage%2C%20cauliflower%2C%20and%20broccoli.%20Root%20vegetables%20include%20carrots%20in%20orange%2C%20red%2C%20and%20black%20varieties%2C%20beets%2C%20and%20potatoes.%20The%20farm%20also%20boasts%20gourds%20like%20ridge%20gourd%2C%20bottle%20gourd%2C%20snake%20gourd%2C%20and%20ash%20gourd%2C%20as%20well%20as%20nightshades%20such%20as%20heirloom%20tomatoes%2C%20brinjals%20of%20different%20varieties%2C%20and%20chillies.%3C%2Fp%3